<i>She didn't file taxes.
She didn't take care of business.</i>

01:19:51.831 --> 01:19:53.540
<i>She lost the house in Mount Vernon.</i>

01:19:53.625 --> 01:19:55.918
Everything went crazy.

01:19:56.878 --> 01:20:01.756
ROGER: <i>She lived a nomadic life,</i>
<i>having no manager, having no husband...</i>

01:20:01.841 --> 01:20:06.469
<i>but she always said living in Africa
was the happiest time in her life.</i>

01:20:06.554 --> 01:20:10.807
<i>She could just be there, enjoy herself.
She didn't have to sing at all.</i>

01:20:10.892 --> 01:20:14.436
LISA: <i>She wasn't playing piano</i>
<i>and she wasn't performing.</i>

01:20:14.521 --> 01:20:17.939
She said she hated the piano.
She hated it.

01:20:18.024 --> 01:20:21.278
Think about it. She's playing since
she was four years old.

01:20:22.194 --> 01:20:23.278
ROGER: <i>On the other hand,</i>

01:20:23.363 --> 01:20:27.282
<i>she was very well aware
that in Africa, no money came in.</i>

01:20:27.367 --> 01:20:29.327
<i>So she had to pick up her career again.</i>

01:20:30.787 --> 01:20:33.996
<i>She didn't want to return
to what she called,</i>

01:20:34.081 --> 01:20:36.249
"The United Snakes of America."

01:20:36.334 --> 01:20:41.128
<i>So she moved to Switzerland,
which was the complete opposite of Africa,</i>

01:20:41.213 --> 01:20:44.342
<i>and the first thing she did
was the Montreux concert.</i>

01:20:46.052 --> 01:20:47.887
[AUDIENCE APPLAUDING]

01:21:09.909 --> 01:21:11.286
You on yet?

01:21:13.162 --> 01:21:15.955
Do you hear all those noises?

01:21:16.040 --> 01:21:17.999
You didn't forget me, huh?

01:21:18.084 --> 01:21:21.796
That's... That's what's so wild,
you didn't forget me.

01:21:24.256 --> 01:21:26.175
I didn't expect you to,

01:21:28.010 --> 01:21:30.221
but I'm tired.

01:21:32.264 --> 01:21:34.100
You don't know what I mean.

01:21:36.353 --> 01:21:39.271
And there are many people
in show business who said,

01:21:39.356 --> 01:21:41.814
"Oh, she... You know,
she used to be a star.

01:21:41.899 --> 01:21:44.025
She's gone all the way to the bottom,"

01:21:44.110 --> 01:21:48.030
and all kinds of crap
which means nothing to me at all.

01:21:49.115 --> 01:21:53.576
I hope that you will see me
or see the spirit

01:21:53.661 --> 01:21:58.248
in another sphere, on another plane
very soon now.

01:21:58.333 --> 01:22:01.459
And again, I don't wanna let you down
and I get this feeling.

01:22:01.544 --> 01:22:05.838
So I think the only way
to tell you who I am these days...

01:22:05.923 --> 01:22:10.470
is to sing a song by Janis Ian.

01:22:13.806 --> 01:22:18.268
<i># Stars, they come and go #</i>

01:22:18.353 --> 01:22:21.188
<i># They come fast, they come slow #</i>

01:22:22.148 --> 01:22:27.319
<i># They go like the last light of the sun,
all in a blaze #</i>

01:22:27.404 --> 01:22:29.737
Hey, girl, sit down!

01:22:29.822 --> 01:22:31.113
Sit down!

01:22:31.198 --> 01:22:32.950
[SCATTERED LAUGHTER]

01:22:36.788 --> 01:22:38.080
Sit down!

01:22:45.838 --> 01:22:49.466
<i># Stars, they come and go #</i>

01:22:49.551 --> 01:22:51.801
<i># They come fast, they come slow #</i>

01:22:51.886 --> 01:22:56.724
<i># They go like the last light of the sun,
all in a blaze #</i>

01:22:57.850 --> 01:23:00.478
<i># All you see is glory #</i>

01:23:02.104 --> 01:23:07.985
<i># But it gets lonely there
when there's no one there to share #</i>

01:23:09.654 --> 01:23:12.364
<i># You can shake it away #</i>

01:23:17.078 --> 01:23:19.872
<i># If you'll hear a story #</i>

01:23:25.628 --> 01:23:28.297
<i># People lust for fame #</i>

01:23:30.007 --> 01:23:32.427
<i># Like athletes in a game #</i>

01:23:36.681 --> 01:23:41.393
<i># They break their collarbones
and come up swinging #</i>

01:23:42.895 --> 01:23:45.438
<i># Some of them are crowned #</i>

01:23:45.523 --> 01:23:47.734
<i># Some of them are downed #</i>

01:23:49.235 --> 01:23:53.072
<i># Some are lost and never found #</i>

01:23:59.746 --> 01:24:02.499
<i># But most have seen it all #</i>

01:24:06.628 --> 01:24:11.924
<i># They live their lives in sad cafés
and music halls #</i>

01:24:17.847 --> 01:24:20.266
<i># And they always have a story #</i>

01:24:25.938 --> 01:24:29.942
<i># Some make it when they're young #</i>

01:24:31.861 --> 01:24:35.948
<i># Before the world has done
its dirty job #</i>

01:24:37.700 --> 01:24:41.746
<i># And later on someone will say,
"You've had your day #</i>

01:24:44.624 --> 01:24:46.876
<i># Now you must make way" #</i>

01:24:50.212 --> 01:24:51.964
<i># Don't they always? #</i>

01:24:52.674 --> 01:24:56.343
<i># But you'll never know the pain #</i>

01:24:58.596 --> 01:25:02.517
<i># Of using a name you never owned #</i>

01:25:04.727 --> 01:25:10.316
<i># The years of forgetting
what you know too well #</i>

01:25:12.610 --> 01:25:17.029
<i># That you who gave the crown
have been let down #</i>

01:25:17.114 --> 01:25:21.703
<i># You try to make amends #</i>

01:25:24.581 --> 01:25:28.125
<i># Without defending #</i>

01:25:29.418 --> 01:25:31.337
<i># Perhaps #</i>

01:25:33.715 --> 01:25:38.886
<i># Pretending you never saw the eyes #</i>

01:25:39.762 --> 01:25:42.138
NINA: <i>In Switzerland,</i>
<i>there I had no money.</i>

01:25:42.223 --> 01:25:44.181
<i>I never got anything from Andy.</i>

01:25:44.266 --> 01:25:47.602
<i>He just cut himself off from me
and I was left high and dry.</i>

01:25:47.687 --> 01:25:52.815
<i>So I left Switzerland and I went to Paris,
thinking that I could resume my career.</i>

01:25:52.900 --> 01:25:54.526
<i>I did it alone</i>

01:25:54.611 --> 01:25:58.154
<i>and I landed in the wrong place.</i>

01:25:58.239 --> 01:26:02.869
<i>I was working every night
in a small cafe for about $300 a night.</i>

01:26:03.661 --> 01:26:05.246
[STAMMERING]

01:26:06.080 --> 01:26:07.414
[SPEAKING FRENCH]

01:26:12.503 --> 01:26:15.046
No, we just do "Vous Etes Seuls."

01:26:15.131 --> 01:26:16.297
It goes like this!

01:26:16.382 --> 01:26:21.803
[SINGING "VOUS ÊTES SEUL,
MAIS JE DÉSIRE ÊTRE AVEC VOUS"]

01:26:21.888 --> 01:26:25.264
NINA: <i>I was desperate</i>
<i>and no one believed that I was there.</i>

01:26:25.349 --> 01:26:28.935
<i>I was too big to be there.
No one came to see me.</i>

01:26:29.020 --> 01:26:31.731
<i>And I had fallen from grace.</i>

01:26:32.774 --> 01:26:38.945
I'm sorry that I didn't become
the world's first black classic pianist.

01:26:39.030 --> 01:26:41.614
I think I would have been happier.

01:26:41.699 --> 01:26:44.826
I'm not very happy now.

01:26:44.911 --> 01:26:48.204
<i>I wouldn't change being part
of the civil rights movement.</i>

01:26:48.289 --> 01:26:49.706
<i>I wouldn't change that.</i>

01:26:49.791 --> 01:26:52.750
<i>But some of the songs that I sang
have hurt my career.</i>

01:26:52.835 --> 01:26:58.255
All of the controversial songs
the industry decided to punish me for...

01:26:58.340 --> 01:27:01.217
and they put a boycott
on all of my records,

01:27:01.302 --> 01:27:03.680
and it's, uh...

01:27:05.139 --> 01:27:07.974
hard for me to incorporate
those songs anymore

01:27:08.059 --> 01:27:09.767
because they are
not relevant to the times.

01:27:09.852 --> 01:27:13.730
In terms of the civil rights movement,
how far have we come?

01:27:13.815 --> 01:27:15.274
There aren't any civil rights!

01:27:16.442 --> 01:27:17.609
What do you mean?

01:27:17.694 --> 01:27:21.403
There is no reason to sing those songs.
Nothing is happening.

01:27:21.488 --> 01:27:24.408
There's no civil rights movement.
Everybody's gone.

01:27:25.910 --> 01:27:30.872
GERRIT DE BRUIN: <i>I met Nina in 1967</i>
<i>and I've been her friend all her life.</i>

01:27:30.957 --> 01:27:34.333
<i>She called me in 1982
and she was here in Paris,</i>

01:27:34.418 --> 01:27:37.754
living in a very small apartment,
hardly with any money.

01:27:37.839 --> 01:27:42.174
She did concerts of four hours long
at Trois Mailletz, that nightclub,

01:27:42.259 --> 01:27:44.595
and she got a few hundred dollars a night.

01:27:45.304 --> 01:27:47.304
<i>And that was the worst period.</i>

01:27:47.389 --> 01:27:51.726
<i>I visited her in that little apartment
and it was so dirty,</i>

01:27:51.811 --> 01:27:56.022
<i>so I cleaned it all up and,
"Nina, you can't live like this,"</i>

01:27:56.107 --> 01:27:58.192
but at that moment,
she was still uncontrollable.

01:27:59.110 --> 01:28:01.402
<i>This thing in the Grand Hotel
in Paris happened.</i>

01:28:01.487 --> 01:28:03.780
<i>Somebody looked her
in the eyes a bit too long,</i>

01:28:03.865 --> 01:28:10.036
and she was already a bit nervous
and she kind of... made a movement

01:28:10.121 --> 01:28:12.163
and I thought, "She's going to hit him."

01:28:12.248 --> 01:28:13.706
Immediately, my arms around her,

01:28:13.791 --> 01:28:18.087
and I dragged her out in a taxi
and I said to the taxi driver, "Drive!"

01:28:19.421 --> 01:28:24.383
AL: <i>When I saw her in Paris, she was like</i>
<i>a street urchin dressed in rags.</i>

01:28:24.468 --> 01:28:29.223
I couldn't believe what was happening
and I was really, really sad.

01:28:29.891 --> 01:28:32.850
<i>Gerrit and I, we knew
something was very wrong,</i>

01:28:32.935 --> 01:28:35.269
<i>and we were trying to figure out,</i>

01:28:35.354 --> 01:28:37.982
and like, "What is it?
What is it, really?"

01:28:39.776 --> 01:28:44.153
<i>So Gerrit found her a condo
in Nijmegen in Holland,</i>

01:28:44.238 --> 01:28:48.950
<i>and Gerrit had a friend, a doctor,
that he brought to Nina's place,</i>

01:28:49.035 --> 01:28:51.953
<i>and the doctor examined her
and asked her questions,</i>

01:28:52.038 --> 01:28:55.039
and he prescribed a medication

01:28:55.124 --> 01:28:58.669
which was kind of new... new spectrum,
called Trilafon.

01:28:59.711 --> 01:29:03.630
LISA: <i>It wasn't till I was in my 20s</i>
<i>and I went to visit her in Nijmegen,</i>

01:29:03.715 --> 01:29:07.719
<i>that's when I learned the term
"manic-depressive" and "bipolar"</i>

01:29:07.804 --> 01:29:08.803
<i>and I remember asking,</i>

01:29:08.888 --> 01:29:10.680
<i>"Well, what is that?
What do you mean by that?"</i>

01:29:10.765 --> 01:29:12.473
And her mood swings

01:29:12.558 --> 01:29:15.142
and a lot of the things
I dealt with earlier in life

01:29:15.227 --> 01:29:16.769
when, you know, one minute she'd be happy

01:29:16.854 --> 01:29:19.438
and then the next minute...

01:29:19.523 --> 01:29:23.650
I'd be dealing with someone
that wasn't in the room five minutes ago.

01:29:23.735 --> 01:29:26.570
<i>It started to make sense.</i>

01:29:26.655 --> 01:29:29.615
GERRIT: <i>She got so deep</i>
<i>in the shit in the end</i>

01:29:29.700 --> 01:29:33.703
<i>that she realized
it's either dying or give in.</i>

01:29:33.788 --> 01:29:36.538
<i>And she gave in because we said, "Nina...</i>

01:29:36.623 --> 01:29:40.835
we'll get you a house,
we'll get you your musicians,

01:29:40.920 --> 01:29:43.880
we'll make the things
all right around you,

01:29:43.965 --> 01:29:46.382
we'll book your concerts...

01:29:46.467 --> 01:29:49.095
but you have to do as we say.

01:29:50.096 --> 01:29:52.847
<i>You have to take your medicine.
You have to work.</i>

01:29:52.932 --> 01:29:56.725
<i>God has given you the possibility
to be able to do what you do, so do it!</i>

01:29:56.810 --> 01:30:00.062
<i>The only thing we want to hear
is either 'yes' or 'no.'"</i>

01:30:00.147 --> 01:30:03.775
<i>And she said,
with tears in her eyes, "Yes."</i>

01:30:04.776 --> 01:30:05.902
LISA: <i>When I saw her,</i>

01:30:05.987 --> 01:30:09.822
I was very concerned because
she had a... a nervous tic.

01:30:09.907 --> 01:30:12.867
You know,
she'd be talking or sitting and this...

01:30:12.952 --> 01:30:14.869
Her mouth would always be twitching,

01:30:14.954 --> 01:30:18.330
and when she would walk,
it was more of a shuffle.

01:30:18.415 --> 01:30:20.666
And I'm like, "What's going on here?"

01:30:20.751 --> 01:30:22.960
You know, "Why...

01:30:23.045 --> 01:30:25.254
What's going on? What am I missing?"

01:30:25.339 --> 01:30:27.091
And they had her on medication.

01:30:28.134 --> 01:30:31.343
AL: <i>She started taking the Trilafon</i>
<i>and the doctor said,</i>

01:30:31.428 --> 01:30:35.347
"Through the years, it's going
to have an effect on her motor skills.

01:30:35.432 --> 01:30:40.895
Her voice is going to start to slur
and her piano abilities will decline.

01:30:40.980 --> 01:30:42.354
<i>You can deal with that</i>

01:30:42.439 --> 01:30:48.154
<i>or you can deal with her probably
damaging herself or someone else."</i>

01:30:49.530 --> 01:30:51.989
<i>But the Trilafon really helped.</i>

01:30:52.074 --> 01:30:53.866
I mean, there were times in Holland,

01:30:53.951 --> 01:30:57.078
sitting on her terrace
in these lounge chairs

01:30:57.163 --> 01:30:58.537
and just holding hands...

01:30:58.622 --> 01:31:01.707
I mean, she was like... She was my sister.

01:31:01.792 --> 01:31:06.380
...and not talking at all for hours,
just enjoying the day.

01:31:08.549 --> 01:31:11.884
LISA: <i>And I suppose that medication</i>
<i>enabled her to perform</i>

01:31:11.969 --> 01:31:15.262
<i>and fulfill the business dealings
that were taking place</i>

01:31:15.347 --> 01:31:17.890
<i>so that her career
could get back on track,</i>

01:31:17.975 --> 01:31:21.185
but there were times when I questioned that,
you know, "But what about her heart?"

01:31:21.270 --> 01:31:25.356
<i>Because at the end of the day,
you guys got wives and husbands and lives,</i>

01:31:25.441 --> 01:31:27.109
<i>but she's alone.</i>

01:31:29.111 --> 01:31:32.321
NINA: <i>My personal life is a shambles.</i>

01:31:32.406 --> 01:31:37.493
<i>I've had a few love affairs
and I would love to be married,</i>

01:31:37.578 --> 01:31:41.999
but everything has had
to be sacrificed for the music.

01:31:46.628 --> 01:31:49.090
[CROWD CHEERING AND APPLAUDING]

01:31:53.970 --> 01:31:57.221
GERRIT: <i>We had to do, first in Holland,</i>
<i>eight concerts,</i>

01:31:57.306 --> 01:32:00.099
<i>and the word spread
that Nina's doing the job well.</i>

01:32:00.184 --> 01:32:03.685
Then she was on the road again
and it was... poof.

01:32:03.770 --> 01:32:05.022
The business was going.

01:32:07.191 --> 01:32:08.232
ROGER: <i>She came onstage</i>

01:32:08.317 --> 01:32:11.986
and you had this overwhelming,
emotional feeling

01:32:12.071 --> 01:32:16.117
coming from the audience
just because she was there.

01:32:17.618 --> 01:32:20.619
Now listen to me.

01:32:20.704 --> 01:32:22.121
I love you very much.

01:32:22.206 --> 01:32:25.832
I think you know that
and I know that you love me.

01:32:25.917 --> 01:32:27.334
- I know that.
- [AUDIENCE MEMBER WHOOPS]

01:32:27.419 --> 01:32:30.087
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

01:32:30.172 --> 01:32:31.255
ROGER: <i>And we never knew too well</i>

01:32:31.340 --> 01:32:33.800
what was going to happen
and how the mood would be.

01:32:34.468 --> 01:32:38.054
So this place is very hot
and it's very crowded

01:32:38.139 --> 01:32:39.846
and it's very ugly.

01:32:39.931 --> 01:32:41.392
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

01:32:43.477 --> 01:32:46.103
ROGER: <i>But she opened her heart and soul</i>

01:32:46.188 --> 01:32:47.521
<i>at that moment.</i>

01:32:47.606 --> 01:32:50.734
That's this special kind of connection
she had with an audience.

01:32:51.568 --> 01:32:54.446
This song is popular all over France.

01:32:55.197 --> 01:32:57.239
It's from our first album...

01:32:57.324 --> 01:33:00.117
the very first album
we made in this world,

01:33:00.202 --> 01:33:02.954
which is at least 25 years old.

01:33:03.039 --> 01:33:05.164
I only wish I was as wise...

01:33:05.249 --> 01:33:08.835
could have been as wise then
as I have become now.

01:33:10.212 --> 01:33:11.547
I have suffered.

01:33:12.631 --> 01:33:16.300
But there's a Bösendorfer here,
so we'll see what happens.

01:33:16.385 --> 01:33:18.137
"My Baby Just Cares For Me."

01:33:25.061 --> 01:33:27.394
She was helped by
"My Baby Just Cares For Me,"

01:33:27.479 --> 01:33:31.482
that song that became a hit
because of the Chanel advertisement.

01:33:31.567 --> 01:33:34.610
NINA: <i>And when "My Baby</i>
<i>Just Cares For Me" came along, I said,</i>

01:33:34.695 --> 01:33:38.155
<i>"I have to take this opportunity now
to go all over the world</i>

01:33:38.240 --> 01:33:40.407
<i>because this is my last chance."</i>

01:33:40.492 --> 01:33:44.495
<i>And so I worked very hard
to take advantage of my second coming</i>

01:33:44.580 --> 01:33:47.458
<i>because it was my last time
as far as I was concerned.</i>

01:33:49.585 --> 01:33:52.044
<i># My baby don't care for clothes #</i>

01:33:52.129 --> 01:33:55.424
<i># My baby don't care for shows #</i>

01:33:56.425 --> 01:34:00.346
<i># My baby just cares for me #</i>

01:34:03.014 --> 01:34:06.185
<i># My baby don't care for... #</i>

01:34:07.644 --> 01:34:10.396
<i># cars and races #</i>

01:34:10.481 --> 01:34:13.066
<i># My baby don't care for... #</i>

01:34:14.860 --> 01:34:16.945
<i># high-tone places #</i>

01:34:18.029 --> 01:34:20.866
<i># Liz Taylor is not his style #</i>

01:34:21.783 --> 01:34:24.536
<i># And even Sally Burton's smile #</i>

01:34:25.829 --> 01:34:29.373
LISA: <i>And she was happiest doing music.</i>
<i>I think that was her salvation.</i>

01:34:29.458 --> 01:34:31.875
<i>That's the one thing that
she didn't have to think about.</i>

01:34:31.960 --> 01:34:35.129
<i>When she sat at the piano,
her fingers could fly.</i>

01:34:35.214 --> 01:34:37.883
<i># My baby don't care who knows it #</i>

01:34:39.343 --> 01:34:40.717
<i># My baby just cares for me #</i>

01:34:40.802 --> 01:34:42.053
<i>She was an anomaly.</i>

01:34:42.138 --> 01:34:44.388
<i>She was a genius. She was brilliant,</i>

01:34:44.473 --> 01:34:49.768
and that brilliance shone through
no matter what she was going through.

01:34:49.853 --> 01:34:53.564
Even into her old age, she was brilliant.

01:34:53.649 --> 01:34:56.858
<i># My baby don't care for clothes #</i>

01:34:56.943 --> 01:35:00.237
<i># My baby don't care for shows #</i>

01:35:00.322 --> 01:35:03.157
GERRIT: <i>She was genius.</i>
<i>She could do whatever she liked.</i>

01:35:03.242 --> 01:35:05.576
<i>And when she didn't have her medicine,</i>

01:35:05.661 --> 01:35:09.039
<i>she, musically,
could get even further out.</i>

01:35:09.998 --> 01:35:12.543
<i># My baby don't care for... #</i>

01:35:14.461 --> 01:35:17.213
<i># high-tone places #</i>

01:35:17.298 --> 01:35:19.506
In one of those little concerts,
and it's recorded,

01:35:19.591 --> 01:35:23.177
<i>she starts playing one song
and she sings another.</i>

01:35:23.262 --> 01:35:25.929
And this recording, I made Miles Davis...

01:35:26.014 --> 01:35:29.391
while we were on tour, we were
on the same jazz tour as Miles Davis,

01:35:29.476 --> 01:35:30.976
and I made him listen to it,

01:35:31.061 --> 01:35:34.355
and he said, "Gerrit...
let me listen to it again!

01:35:34.440 --> 01:35:36.607
How is she doing this?"

01:35:36.692 --> 01:35:38.109
He couldn't understand.

01:35:38.194 --> 01:35:42.406
<i># My baby just cares for me #</i>

01:35:44.825 --> 01:35:49.161
SHABAZZ: <i>As I got older, I started</i>
<i>to look at her and I thought to myself,</i>

01:35:49.246 --> 01:35:52.248
<i>"Wow, she's from another time!"</i>

01:35:52.333 --> 01:35:56.837
But she was not at odds with the times.
The times was at odds with her.

01:35:57.504 --> 01:36:04.345
<i>I think when a person moves
to their own kind of clock, spirit, flow,</i>

01:36:05.304 --> 01:36:09.640
<i>if we were living in an environment
that allowed us to be exactly who we are,</i>

01:36:09.725 --> 01:36:11.808
<i>you're always in congress with yourself.</i>

01:36:11.893 --> 01:36:13.519
<i>The challenge is,</i>

01:36:13.604 --> 01:36:16.772
<i>"How do we fit in in the world
that we're around, but we...</i>

01:36:16.857 --> 01:36:19.733
<i>Are we allowed to be exactly who we are?</i>

01:36:19.818 --> 01:36:24.573
<i>Was Nina Simone allowed
to be exactly who she was?"</i>

01:36:25.782 --> 01:36:28.784
<i>As fragile as she was strong,</i>

01:36:28.869 --> 01:36:32.538
<i>as vulnerable as she was dynamic,</i>

01:36:32.623 --> 01:36:35.374
<i>she was African royalty.</i>

01:36:35.459 --> 01:36:39.211
How does royalty stomp around in the mud

01:36:39.296 --> 01:36:41.423
and still walk with grace?

01:36:42.215 --> 01:36:46.845
<i>Most people are afraid
to be as honest as she lived.</i>

01:36:47.513 --> 01:36:50.140
<i># My baby just cares for... #</i>

01:36:51.267 --> 01:36:54.311
<i># He just says he cares for... #</i>

01:36:55.271 --> 01:36:58.857
<i># My baby just cares for me #</i>

